Rodel Flordeliz is the multi-talented host and producer of the award-winning livelihood show Bread n’ Butter.<b> </b>A homegrown talent of UNTV, Rodel started as a computer specialist, having a degree in Computer Engineering.  He was soon discovered for his voice-over skills and continued to work as an off-cam talent.  Gaining confidence, he later tried on-cam duties as a field reporter for "Ito Ang Balita" in SBN 21. It has always been his dream to work in front of the camera and when the opportunity came, he took it like a duck to water.

Rodel was nominated twice at the PMPC Star Awards for Best Travel Show Host (Bread n’ Butter) in 2009 and Best Morning Show Host (Good Morning Kuya) in 2012. His dark good looks have also earned him modeling stints for print ads and TV commercials.  His talent extends to the visual arts too as he currently supervises UNTV’s Creative Department.

&nbsp;

Born to the philanthropist and movie star, Ms. Rosa Rosal, Toni Rose Gayda was destined to work in front of a camera despite her mother’s objection to her joining show business.  She started her career as a model and was selected to join the über exclusive league of Camay Girls.  She also starred in various films in the ‘70’s, but it was in hosting that she found her niche.

In the mid 80’s Toni Rose joined “Lunch Date,” a noontime variety show at GMA 7. Her natural comedic timing and light-hearted stage presence endeared her to viewers, earning her a place among Philippine TV’s most respected and well-loved television hosts.  Her hosting career has seen her work with different networks.  She was in “It’s A Real Deal” at PTV4 and “Skin Deep” at TV5.  In 2011, Toni Rose joined the Kasangbahay network of UNTV as the co-host of A Song of Praise (ASOP), a song writing competition.  She shares the stage with balladeer Richard Reynoso and their wacky tandem makes for a lively and entertaining show every Sunday night.

